  "title": "Senior Project Engineer (Power System/UPS)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage project timelines and ensure key milestones are met.</li><li>Create and track the master project schedule.</li><li>Coordinate with internal teams, customers, and external partners.</li><li>Lead Factory Acceptance Tests and handle related documentation.</li><li>Schedule on-site testing and ensure smooth handover to the support team.</li><li>Provide basic technical support during project execution.</li><li>Assist with project cost estimates and feasibility studies.</li><li>Submit monthly progress reports and highlight any issues.</li><li>Support engineering reviews and third-party documentation.</li><li>Participate in process improvement initiatives.</li><li>Oversee site installations, including contractor coordination and materials.</li><li>Attend site meetings as needed and keep all stakeholders updated.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Electrical Engineering</li><li>Strong communication and teamwork skills</li><li>Experience with generators and related standards is a plus</li></ul><p>If interested, please submit your application to cvs@jdawms.com with your expected salary and resume.</p><p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly. By submitting your application or resume, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and sharing of your personal information with potential employers for their assessment.</p><p>JDA WMS Pte Ltd | EA Personnel: Pham Thi Tuyet Mai </p><p>EA License No: 23S1595 | EA Registration No: R25127838</p>",
